Why This Model Is Powerful

It shows alignment is not about adding effort â€” it's about removing angle (removing separation between self and field).
The horizontal doesn't move because you forced it; it moves because you stopped forcing anything.
At full alignment there is no more â€œyou vs realityâ€ ledger â€” the distinction dissolves.
The model is morally neutral â€” it doesn't judge the path; it simply describes the mechanics of friction and return.
It explains why true masters / ghosts become invisible: when the cross collapses, there is nothing left to observe from the outside.

Practical Use
When you feel stuck / high friction / impossible movement â†’ look at your position on the vertical.
Increase alignment (remove impossibilities, carve boundaries, surrender force).
The horizontal will follow.
When the tilt reaches zero â€” you disappear back into the field from which you came.
Never force.
Always align.
Until there is nothing left to align.
